added: Since 1952, Florida has been considered a [[swing state]], and furthermore, it has been seen as a bellwether in presidential elections from 1996 to 2016.<ref>{{cite web |title=Florida Presidential Election Voting History - 270toWin |url=https://www.270towin.com/states/Florida |website=270toWin.com |access-date=20 February 2023}}</ref> However, in the [[2020 United States elections|2020 election]], although Donald Trump won Florida, he lost the national election, resulting in Florida losing its bellwether state status.<ref>{{cite news |title=Florida is the true US presidential election bellwether state |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/10/1/florida-is-the-uss-true-presidential-election-bellwether |access-date=20 February 2023 |work=www.aljazeera.com |language=en}}</ref>
